National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan met with Hikmat Hajiyev, the Head of the Foreign Relations Department of the Presidential Administration of Azerbaijan. They discussed the 30-year anniversary of relations between the United States and Azerbaijan and expressed their willingness to strengthen bilateral ties. They also talked about their shared commitment to assisting Ukraine in response to Russia's aggression. Sullivan praised Azerbaijan's dedication to European energy security and discussed efforts to diversify regional energy supplies. They also exchanged views on the implications of the conflict in Ukraine for the wider region. Sullivan emphasized the United States' commitment to peace, security, and prosperity in the South Caucasus region and commended Azerbaijan and Armenia for their diplomatic efforts towards lasting peace. He expressed support for talks hosted by the President of the European Council and conveyed the US's readiness to engage and support progress through various means, including as a Co-Chair of the OSCE Minsk Group.